<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-425-133  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 425 133.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 31 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Landmark Graphics restructures and changes direction.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Landmark Graphics Corp. (management).andO;Ticker:    LMRK.andO;Topic:     Software PublishersReorganizationWork Force ReductionMarketing Strategy.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>LANDMARK GRAPHICS RESTRUCTURES AND CHANGES DIRECTION HOUSTON, TEXAS, U.S.A.,andO;1990 JUL 27 (NB) -- Landmark Graphics Corp. has announced that it has reducedits staff of 335 employees by 25.andP;  The 25 positions were eliminated,according to Landmark, because of changes in the business direction of thefirm.andM;Landmark President and CEO C.E.andP;  Ennis said the reduction is an adjustment tofundamental changes in the computer-aided exploration (CAEX) business, andwas not motivated by financial performance or reduced expectations.andP;  Thosechanges, Ennis explained, include the increasing ability of standardoff-the-shelf computers to run the company's geoscience software, andincreased globalization of the oil business.andM;Landmark has no plans for further reductions, Ennis says.andP;  He adds theoverall impact of Landmark's organizational changes is to put the company inthe best possible position to take advantage of continued industry growth.andO;&quot;Our expectations of the fiscal 1991 market opportunities, and Landmark'sability to seize them, are as high as ever,&quot; Ennis said.andM;Bob Peebler, Landmark spokesperson, explained the organizational changesfurther in a discussion with Newsbytes, &quot;We had previously done much morehardware integration work which required engineering and mechanical work.andO;When we moved our primary delivery system from the IBM RT to the standard SunWorkstation, we were able to take advantage of already existing hardware andconcentrate primarily on our software.andP;  Similarly, the use of Unix and Motifallowed us to concentrate on our strength, the provision of our applicationssoftware, rather than have to concern ourselves with user interfaces andspecial software drivers.andP;  We will soon be adding the IBM R6000 system to ourproduct line but that will  provide no more difficulty than the Sun.andP;  As longas we adhere to industry standard hardware, operating systems and userinterfaces, we can devote all of our energies to our CAEX software.andP;  It wasthis redirection that allowed us to streamline our organization.&quot;andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/199000728/Press Contact: Bob Peebler,Landmark, 713-579-4700.andO;</TEXT></DOC>